<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="399" pageId="0" pageNumber="397" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1699,2034]" box="[151,596,1734,1757]" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,417,1734,1757]" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">
Description (
<typeStatus box="[297,405,1734,1757]" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">Holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity box="[514,592,1734,1757]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="0" pageNumber="397" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1699,2034]" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis box="[199,264,1767,1791]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">Head.</emphasis>
Ground colour of integument black, densely covered by fine, thick silvery-grey setae with the exception of a large, black, setose, circular spot close to occipital margin. Eyes quite large, hairy and finely facetted, reaching occiput. Mouthparts paler than remaining integument, covered by slightly golden pubescence. Maxillary palpi brown with last segment shaped like an isosceles triangle. Antennae moderately long, weakly serrate, reaching elytral humeri. Last antennal segment ellipsoidal, 1.4× length of tenth segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1699,2034]" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis box="[199,312,1942,1965]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="397">Pronotum.</emphasis>
Ground colour of integument black, entirely covered by silvery setae similar to those of head, except for longitudinal black band extending along median line from occipital margin to posterior lobe of pronotum, and two black circular lateral patches.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="398" startId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" targetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" targetPageId="1">
