<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" box="[199,956,151,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis box="[199,311,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<taxonomicName box="[199,308,151,175]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scutellum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[317,425,152,175]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scutellum</taxonomicName>
triangular, densely covered by silvery-grey setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis box="[199,273,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Elytra.</emphasis>
Elytra long and slender, length 2.5× maximum width at humeri. Ground colour of integument black; black patches on elytra densely covered with black setae. Elytral humeral band XX shaped (
<emphasis box="[1062,1122,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1127,1300,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1841" refString="Takakuwa, M. (2000) A taxonomic study of the mordellid subgenus Stenoglipa (Coleoptera, Mordellidae). Bulletin of the Kanagawa Prefectural Museum. Natural Science, 29, 53 - 105." type="journal article">Takakuwa 2000</bibRefCitation>
), developing from humeral callus for 1/5 of elytral length, covered by dense, silvery-white setae. Median elytral band consisting of an almost C-shaped pattern of white setae surrounding patch of black setae. Apical elytral band small (width 1.2× length), formed from dense silvery-white pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[645,730,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[204,1388,194,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype; B Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000, Holotype; C Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura, 1967, non-type (male and female); D Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype, paramera; E Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000,Holotype,paramera; F Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura,1967,non-type, paramera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis box="[199,272,360,383]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Venter.</emphasis>
Ground colour of the integument black, covered by sparse, silvery-white pubescence. Profemora pale orange-brown, protibiae and medial legs black. Hind legs black; all legs covered by same pubescence as remainder of body. Pygidium very long, pointed and strongly keeled dorsally; length 6× basal width and 3× length of hypopygidium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis box="[199,307,463,487]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Parameres asymmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[590,674,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[204,1388,194,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype; B Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000, Holotype; C Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura, 1967, non-type (male and female); D Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype, paramera; E Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000,Holotype,paramera; F Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura,1967,non-type, paramera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Left paramere U-shaped, with parallel branches. Major branch length 1.4× length of minor. Major branch apex rounded, expanded and flattened. Minor branch straight. Right paramere straight, Y-shaped. Minor branch situated at inner margin of the paramere, at 3/5 of total paramere length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Variability.</emphasis>
All the 
<typeStatus box="[425,527,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">paratypes</typeStatus>
are homogeneous both in terms of size and colour, differing very little from the 
<typeStatus box="[151,248,602,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">holotype</typeStatus>
; dimensions are included in the 16 ± 
<quantity box="[646,707,602,625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
range while the only variation in the chromatic pattern concerns the medial elytral band which in some specimens is no longer C-shaped but irregularly defined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="399" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,672,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be included in the 
<taxonomicName box="[753,973,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nipponica" subGenus="Stenoglipa">
<emphasis box="[753,973,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Glipa (S.) nipponica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<emphasis box="[1144,1204,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1211,1382,672,695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1841" refString="Takakuwa, M. (2000) A taxonomic study of the mordellid subgenus Stenoglipa (Coleoptera, Mordellidae). Bulletin of the Kanagawa Prefectural Museum. Natural Science, 29, 53 - 105." type="journal article">Takakuwa 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and associated with 
<taxonomicName authority="Takakuwa, 2000" authorityName="Takakuwa" authorityYear="2000" box="[326,835,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillima" subGenus="Stenoglipa">
<emphasis box="[326,648,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[657,835,706,729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" refId="ref1841" refString="Takakuwa, M. (2000) A taxonomic study of the mordellid subgenus Stenoglipa (Coleoptera, Mordellidae). Bulletin of the Kanagawa Prefectural Museum. Natural Science, 29, 53 - 105." type="journal article">Takakuwa, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[853,936,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[204,1388,194,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype; B Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000, Holotype; C Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura, 1967, non-type (male and female); D Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype, paramera; E Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000,Holotype,paramera; F Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura,1967,non-type, paramera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) from SW Borneo due to the narrowed body profile (in dorsal view), silvery-white pubescence and long pygidium. The new species can be separated from the latter based on the pattern of elytral bands (Fig, 1ĀB) and genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[855,941,775,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[204,1388,194,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype; B Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000, Holotype; C Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura, 1967, non-type (male and female); D Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype, paramera; E Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000,Holotype,paramera; F Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura,1967,non-type, paramera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
̄E); in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruzzier" authorityYear="2018" box="[1026,1144,775,799]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badanoi">
<emphasis box="[1026,1144,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">G. badanoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the median elytral band is almost C-shaped while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takakuwa" authorityYear="2000" box="[435,576,809,833]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillima">
<emphasis box="[435,576,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">G. gracillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the white band profile is much more irregular, with the distal margin produced towards to the elytral apex. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruzzier" authorityYear="2018" box="[468,627,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badanoi">
<emphasis box="[468,627,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Glipa badanoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the sympatric 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="1967" box="[1056,1324,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ishigakiana" subSpecies="kotoensis">
<emphasis box="[1056,1324,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">G. ishigakiana kotoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the following characters: body profile narrow and elongate, pygidium 3× length of hypopygidium in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruzzier" authorityYear="2018" box="[1203,1321,879,903]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badanoi">
<emphasis box="[1203,1321,879,903]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">G. badanoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1337,1422,880,903]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,234,1940,1959]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,209,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[204,1388,194,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. A Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype; B Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000, Holotype; C Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura, 1967, non-type (male and female); D Glipa (Stenoglipa) badanoi n.sp., Holotype, paramera; E Glipa (Stenoglipa) gracillima Takakuwa, 2000,Holotype,paramera; F Glipa (Stenoglipa) ishigakiana kotoensis Nomura,1967,non-type, paramera." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1221510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), body stout and pygidium 2.7× length of hypopygidium in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nomura" authorityYear="1967" box="[776,1036,913,937]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ishigakiana" subSpecies="kotoensis">
<emphasis box="[776,1036,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="399">G. ishigakiana kotoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
